mean_loudness = aggregate(loudness~playlist_name, pastplaylists,mean)


mode_function <- function(x) {
  mode0 <- names(which.max(table(x)))
  if(is.numeric(x)) return(as.numeric(mode0))
  mode0
}
mode_key =  aggregate(key~playlist_name,data=pastplaylists,FUN=mode_function)
mode_mode =  aggregate(mode~playlist_name,data=pastplaylists,FUN=mode_function)
mode_time_signature = aggregate(time_signature~playlist_name,data=pastplaylists,FUN=mode_function)

Loudness is highly correlated with most of the features, and almost perfectly negatively correlated with acousticness and instrumentalness. (We may not need this feature included?) Acousticness is almost perfectly inverse to energy Instrumentalness is negatively correlated with danceability Takeaway: For regression analysis, dont recommending using Loudness or Acousticness, since those are both highly positively and negatively correlated with the other features and we may see multi-colinearity

Regression(s) #6: Combined impact of a song appearing on a playlist in terms days on playlist and # followers of that playlist, and how many songs appear on the playlist
